## MPlayer

### saving rm audio streams

Save the .ram file to a text file.

Open up the textfile, and if the protocol in the URL is pnm://, change it to rtsp://

to save the stream, run:

    mplayer -playlist playlist.txt -ao pcm:file=output.wav -vc dummy -vo null

this saves the output as raw pcm

## MEncoder

Something like this to encode a file into xvid/mp3 (sourced from <http://en.linuxreviews.org/HOWTO_Convert_video_files>)

    mencoder <filename.avi> -ovc xvid -oac mp3lame -xvidencopts bitrate=687 -o <output.avi>

